article.headline: Houston 63, Southern Miss 53
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Brian Latham scored 19 points and Andre Owens added 18 to lead Houston past Southern Mississippi 63-53 Saturday night. Houston (11-6, 2-1 Conference USA) hit eight 3-pointers in the first half to build a double-digit lead. Southern Mississippi (9-7, 0-4) lost its fifth straight game. Owens, who hit four 3-pointers, broke the school record for career 3-pointers with 184. The Cougars hit 11-of-30 shots from three-point range, including 8-of-17 in the first half as they took a 32-22 halftime lead. Michael Ford and Jasper Johnson each had 14 points for the Eagles. Houston's Lanny Smith scored 13 points. Southern Mississippi had 21 turnovers, which Houston turned into 25 points.
